CENBANK Core Router Configuration Documentation
Project Overview
This repository contains the complete configuration for four core-layer routers deployed across four floors of the CENBANK enterprise network. Each router is integrated into a centralized OSPF Area 0 backbone and is secured with SSH access, encrypted credentials, and segmented subnets for optimized routing and security.
üîÅ Common Configuration Features
‚Ä¢ 	Hostname: Core-LayerR
‚Ä¢ 	Password: cisco
‚Ä¢ 	OSPF Area: 0
‚Ä¢ 	SSH Enabled: Yes
‚Ä¢ 	Encrypted Passwords: Yes (Service password-encryption)
‚Ä¢ 	Domain Name: cisco.net
‚Ä¢ 	MOTD Banner: Core-LayerR
‚Ä¢ 	Access Config:
‚Ä¢ 	Console & VTY login with encrypted password
‚Ä¢ 	Transport input restricted to SSH

üìç Floor 1 ‚Äì Core Router Configuration

interface GigabitEthernet0/0

 ip address 10.10.10.1 255.255.255.252
interface GigabitEthernet0/1
 ip address 10.10.10.5 255.255.255.252
interface GigabitEthernet0/2
 ip address 10.10.10.9 255.255.255.252
interface Serial0/2/0
 ip address 10.10.10.13 255.255.255.252
interface Serial0/2/1
 ip address 10.10.10.17 255.255.255.252
 
router ospf 10

 network 10.10.10.0 0.0.0.3 area 0
 network 10.10.10.4 0.0.0.3 area 0
 network 10.10.10.8 0.0.0.3 area 0
 network 10.10.10.12 0.0.0.3 area 0
 network 10.10.10.16 0.0.0.3 area 0

